# ── ML Models — DO NOT IGNORE — must be committed for cloud Docker build ──────
# The .joblib files in backend/ml/models/ MUST be in git so that Render's
# Docker build (which has no access to local Docker volumes) can COPY them
# into the image via "COPY . ." in the backend Dockerfile.
#
# To copy models from the local Docker volume before first push:
#   docker run --rm `
#     -v deploy_breathesafe_ml_models_deploy:/src `
#     -v "C:\Users\<your-username>\deployment_version_pro\deploy_breathesafe\backend\ml\models:/dst" `
#     alpine sh -c "cp -r /src/. /dst/"
# Then: git add backend/ml/models/ && git commit -m "add ML models"

# ── Data files (large CSVs) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The master CSV is not needed in the deploy repo — the DB is seeded via
# seed_data.py and kept current by the backend's automated pipeline.
